\ =============================================================================
\ Mode <-> stage coupling — the actor-dependent half of the mode system.
\ =============================================================================
\ mode.vfx lives in [supershow.core] and is actor-agnostic. This file (loaded in
\ [supershow.actor], after stage.vfx) is the only part that touches the stage
\ system: it binds a mode's stage to the global `actors` stage and points stg@
\ at the active mode's stage. Headerless — compiles into [supershow.actor].
\ =============================================================================

public

\ Future modes inherit the global stage in their template; patch the
\ already-constructed default-mode (built back in mode.vfx, before `actors`).
%mode template { actors stg ! }
default-mode { actors stg ! }

:noname ( - stage )  gamemode @ -> stg @ ; is stg@
